    <item>
      <title>Relational Computer</title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/tech/domains/computing/domains/relational-computing/terms/relational-computer/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/tech/domains/computing/domains/relational-computing/terms/relational-computer/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;date-created-2026-04-27&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#date-created-2026-04-27&#34; class=&#34;heading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Link to this section&#34;&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;rasts-with: boolean-computer&#xA;date-created: 2026-04-27&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;relational computer&lt;/strong&gt; is a &lt;a href=&#34;../../../terms/computer.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;computer&lt;/a&gt; whose primary substrate is the &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../../../../science/domains/information/terms/relation.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;relation&lt;/a&gt;. Its &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../../../../science/domains/information/terms/data.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;data&lt;/a&gt; is encoded as associations between &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../../../../science/domains/information/terms/entity.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;entities&lt;/a&gt;, and its &lt;a href=&#34;../../../terms/computation.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;computation&lt;/a&gt; is the addition, removal, and traversal of those associations in a &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../../../../science/domains/math/terms/graph.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;graph&lt;/a&gt;. The relational computer takes &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../../../../science/domains/relationality/_index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;relationality&lt;/a&gt; as its organizing ontology.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;substrate-and-identity&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#substrate-and-identity&#34; class=&#34;heading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Link to this section&#34;&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;Substrate and identity&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In a relational computer, an entity is constituted by the relations it participates in, not by its location in memory or the value stored at that location. Identity is positional in the graph rather than locational. Two entities are equal when their relational structure is the same; an entity persists when its relations persist; an entity is observed by traversing the &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../../../../science/domains/math/terms/edge.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;edges&lt;/a&gt; incident to it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
